This article discusses an executive order issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. regarding the response to the COVID-19 pandemic in the United States. The order emphasizes the importance of using science and data to guide the response and aims to build a stronger public health infrastructure to prevent, detect, and respond to future biological threats. The heads of all executive departments and agencies are instructed to facilitate the gathering, sharing, and publication of COVID-19-related data, with appropriate protections for confidentiality, privacy, law enforcement, and national security. The order also calls for the enhancement of data collection and collaboration capabilities, the review of public health data systems, and the advancement of innovation in public health data and analytics. The order includes provisions to protect privileged information and does not create any legal rights or benefits.